        // ── Creating Customers (Article) ─────────────────────────────────
        await GetOrCreateModule(new TrainingModule
        {
            Title = "Creating Customers",
            Slug = "customers-creating",
            Summary = "The three ways to create a customer — Quick add, Convert from Lead, and Guided setup — and how to walk through the guided customer wizard at /customers/new.",
            ContentType = TrainingContentType.Article,
            EstimatedMinutes = 6,
            IsPublished = true,
            SortOrder = 5,
            AppRoutes = """["/customers","/customers/new"]""",
            Tags = """["customers","create","onboarding","wizard"]""",
            ContentJson = """{"body":"## Creating Customers\n\nClicking **+ New Customer** on the Customers list page does not jump straight into a form. Instead it opens a small **fork dialog** that asks *how* you want to create the customer. There are three paths, and picking the right one saves time.\n\n### The Three-Way Create Fork\n\nWhen you click **+ New Customer**, the fork dialog presents three cards:\n\n1. **Quick add** (the highlighted, primary choice — lightning-bolt icon, 'Fastest' badge). Opens the original flat dialog: Name, Company Name, Email, Phone, plus optional Credit Limit, Default Currency, and Billing/Shipping addresses. Best when you just need the record in the system *now* and will fill in the rest later. Only **Name** is required.\n2. **Convert from lead** (person-add icon). Opens a **lead picker** — search your existing leads, click one, and the system runs a one-click conversion that creates the customer, links the source lead, and rolls its contacts and outreach preferences forward in a single transaction. Use this whenever a lead already exists so you don't re-key company and contact details.\n3. **Guided setup** (tune icon). Routes to the multi-step guided wizard at `/customers/new`. Best for a net-new customer worth a thorough, structured onboarding (credit terms, tax exemption, addresses captured up front).\n\nClick **Cancel** to back out of the fork without creating anything.\n\n### Path 1 — Quick Add\n\nThe quick dialog is a single screen. Enter the **Name** (required), and optionally Company Name, Email, Phone, Credit Limit, Default Currency, and a billing and/or shipping address. The **Save** button stays disabled until the form is valid; the validation-warning icon next to it lists anything that needs attention. After saving, you land on the new customer's detail page.\n\nNew customers are created **Active** by default, so a brand-new record with no open business shows the **Prospect** tab set until business starts flowing.\n\n### Path 2 — Convert from Lead\n\nChoosing **Convert from lead** opens the lead picker. Type in the search box to filter by company or contact, then click the lead row (it shows the lead's status chip and engagement shape). Conversion is **one click** — there is no longer a multi-step credit/tax/address stepper in the middle. The server creates the customer atomically and navigates you to the new customer's page. Fill in credit limit, tax, and addresses afterward on the detail page using the normal edit flows.\n\n### Path 3 — Guided Setup Wizard (/customers/new)\n\nThe guided wizard uses the shared workflow shell (the same pill-and-chevron stepper used for Parts and Vendors). It has four steps:\n\n1. **Identity** (required) — Name (required), Company Name, Email, Phone. This step materializes the customer record on first save.\n2. **Addresses** (optional) — capture billing and shipping addresses up front.\n3. **Credit & Tax** (optional) — Credit Limit, Default Currency, and a Tax Exempt toggle. Turning on **Tax Exempt** reveals a required **Tax Exemption ID** field.\n4. **Review** (required) — a read-only summary of everything entered. Confirm to finish.\n\nThe wizard offers an **Express** mode toggle that collapses the steps into one consolidated screen for users who want to fill everything at once. Each step saves as you advance, and the URL carries the run state (`?workflow=customer-guided-v1&step=…`) so you can refresh or share the in-progress link without losing work.\n\n### Which Path Should I Use?\n\n- **Just need the record fast?** Quick add.\n- **A lead already exists?** Convert from lead — never re-type what you already captured during acquisition.\n- **Important new account you want set up properly?** Guided setup.\n\nAll three paths end at the same place: the customer's detail page, where the lifecycle-driven tabs take over.","sections":[]}"""
        });

